        p1="Three levels: smart meter with IHD (free from supplier, SMETS2, real-time usage in £ and kWh, half-hourly data). Energy monitoring plugs (TP-Link Kasa £10-£15, Meross £8-£12) measure individual device consumption. Whole-home monitors (Hildebrand Glow £100-£150, Loop £50-£80) connect via HAN port or CT clamps. Octopus Agile tariff offers half-hourly variable rates (cheap 5p/kWh during windy/solar, expensive 50p/kWh peak). Smart home automation enables shifting high-consumption tasks to cheap periods.",
